description.plain:
KIDS SEE GHOSTS was a hip-hop duo consisting of Kanye West and Kid Cudi. The collaborative effort was officially announced by Kanye on April 19, 2018.

Before officially forming KIDS SEE GHOSTS, Kanye and Cudi had an extensive collaborative history, dating back to 2008 when Cudi worked with Ye on the latter’s 808s & Heartbreak. Also, in 2008, Kanye signed Cudi to G.O.O.D. Music.

The two would continue to work on each other’s albums over the next few years until Cudi announced that he had departed from G.O.O.D Music in mid-2013. Although he stated that his departure was on good terms, he also said that he felt “underused.”

The duo did not have much interaction at all over the next two years, but they finally reconnected at some point because Cudi assisted with the creation of The Life of Pablo. “Father Stretch My Hands, Pt. 1,” which was released in February 2016, was their first collaboration on wax since 2013.

Later that year, in September, Kanye and Cudi hit another rough patch in their friendship when Cudi called out Ye and others on Twitter. However, their issues were quickly resolved when Kanye made a peace offering.

Once their issues were ultimately resolved, Kanye and Cudi shared the stage on a few occasions. They reassured their resolution when they were pictured together in Japan in August 2017. This was also the beginning of rumors of a collaborative project in the works.

On the same day that Kanye announced KIDS SEE GHOSTS, he also unveiled the release date of his and Cudi’s eponymous collaborative album. KIDS SEE GHOSTS was ultimately released on June 8, 2018.

After the release of KIDS SEE GHOST, in July 2018, Cudi revealed that him and Ye would continue to release music as KIDS SEE GHOST. In the interview with Billboard, Cudi revealed that the duo had songs that didn’t end up making it to the final cut for their debut album that he hopes to release later. Cudi also confirmed that there would be more music released from the group in a September 2019 interview with Complex.

On April 19, 2022, four years after the announcement of the group, Kid Cudi announced on Twitter that the song “Rock N Roll,” which was landed in Pusha-T’s album IT’S ALMOST DRY, would be his final collaboration with Ye due to the latter artist’s recent behavior, which ultimately dissolved the duo’s partnership. Cuti stated:

I did this song a year ago when I was still cool [with] Kanye. I am not cool [with] that man. He’s not my friend and I only cleared the song for Pusha cuz thats my guy. This is the last song u will hear me on [with] Kanye.

songs.full_title: Reborn by KIDS SEE GHOSTS
songs.title: Reborn

description.plain:
“Reborn” sees Kanye West and Kid Cudi discussing personal issues and moving forward from previous mistakes.

The two artists trade verses and elaborate on their controversial pasts. Leading up to the release of ye, Kanye had been making headlines for voicing support for Donald Trump and calling “slavery a choice,” while Cudi had been battling drug addiction for years.

Two years prior to the release of this song, Cudi shared a letter on his Facebook page acknowledging his mental health issues. Appropriately enough, Cudi stated that he would return from rehabilitation “reborn”:

Love and light to everyone who has love for me and I am sorry if I let anyone down. I really am sorry. Ill be back, stronger, better. Reborn.

It’s not a coincidence that the term “reborn” perfectly describes Kanye and Cudi—the song details the transition the two have gone through. The idea of being reborn is used as a metaphor by Cudi throughout the song, explaining the way both artists have evolved and changed from their past selves.

Sampling Louis Prima’s “What Will Santa Claus Say” to eerie effect, Ye and Cudi touch on everything from accidental anal sex, to Ric Flair and Lacoste.

The sample of “Someday”  by Shirley Ann Lee which appears at the end of the song was also used on “Ghost Town” from Kanye’s 8th album ye.

songs.full_title: Feel the Love by KIDS SEE GHOSTS (Ft. Pusha T)
songs.title: Feel the Love

description.plain:
The opening track of Kanye West’s and Kid Cudi’s first collaborative album, KIDS SEE GHOSTS, features fellow G.O.O.D. Music artist Pusha-T.

Pusha delivers the song’s sole rap verse. Kid Cudi feels the love that is surrounding him, despite the fact that audible gun sounds can be heard throughout the song—courtesy of Mr. West.

The song was first heard at a listening party held in an abandoned ghost town, somewhere in Southern California. It was also available to view in the WAV streaming app on June 7, 2018.
